
1. Ethiopia is home to the lowest place on the African continent, the Danakil Depression.
2. Ethiopia’s Danakil Depression is the hottest place on Earth.
3. Ethiopia is one of just two African countries that are considered to have never been colonised.
4. Ethiopia has upwards of 80 languages spoken across its regions, and as of 2020 it even has 
five official working languages.
5. Many Ethiopians follow an Orthodox Christianity religion which prohibits eating any animal 
products on Wednesday and Friday, which means you’ll almost always find vegetarian dishes on the menu.
